### Breaking changes

There are some breaking changes in this release that significantly improves the test interface.

#### `test()` is now only for synchronous or promise/observable returning tests

The main `test()` interface is now synchronous by default and can be made asynchronous by returning a promise/observable or using a async/generator function (which implicitly returns a promise).

You no longer have to call `t.end()` in synchronous tests:

``` diff
 test(t => {
    t.pass();
-   t.end();
})
```

You can no longer use `test()` for callback-style APIs, so we've introduced a new ["callback mode" `test.cb()`](https://github.com/sindresorhus/ava#testcbtitle-body).

``` diff
-test(t => {
+test.cb(t => {
    fn(err => {
        t.ifError(err);
        t.end();
    });
 });
```

https://github.com/sindresorhus/ava/commit/387c30a056cdd3ef8510262ce2119031c8d18361 https://github.com/sindresorhus/ava/commit/717030813a51d349830e28a7b77b4014837d6eac

#### `t.plan()` will no longer auto-end tests

You will now have to explicitly end tests with callback-style APIs. Previously, `t.plan()` doubled as both an assert counter and ending the test when the assertion count was reached. This was a mistake. It's now only an assert counter. We are now able to warn on too many async assertion which were previously not possible. Note that `t.end()` only works in "callback mode" `test.cb()`.

``` diff
-test(t => {
+test.cb(t => {
    t.plan(1);

    fn(err => {
        t.ifError(err);
+       t.end();
    });
 });
```

More info here: https://github.com/sindresorhus/ava#warning-recent-breaking-change

https://github.com/sindresorhus/ava/commit/f8168153c798fd07e33d120d2a7448c4b8408db0

### Highlights
- Test methods are now [chainable](https://github.com/sindresorhus/ava#chaining-test-modifiers). You can for example do `test.serial.skip()`. https://github.com/sindresorhus/ava/commit/d874ec9642a08492d3dc01ff311c23ddfeaa0797
- Use the local AVA version if available when running `$ ava` from the CLI. https://github.com/sindresorhus/ava/commit/2f7ac92d8ccfd5763e83d5a4050ee0ed23e46a87
- Guard against time manipulation by mocking modules like Sinon. https://github.com/sindresorhus/ava/commit/b88c2baf399a4b09a76cdb6402b0e02669759e42
- Improve the behavior of the `--serial` flag. https://github.com/sindresorhus/ava/commit/7ad7501db2f836cb9200ee018ed8a867119f3113

